  "comments": "Despite the name, the memorial is actually not an arch at all, though it does include two arches. Sculptures on the memorial include Herbert Adams' statue of Richard Smith, who funded the memorial, and Samuel Murray's bust of James H. Windrim, who was the artist and architect of the memorial itself. Detail pictures of the individual pieces are in alphabetical order by subject.  One of John Massey Rhind's eagles is pictured last.  Dahlgren is listed elsewhere as \"Dahlgreen.\"",
